That's helpful. I need to sneak in one more to be a little more granular on the forward outlook for the rest of the fiscal year. Would you think that this would be a trough quarter for the combined computing business or is there still some of that legacy business that might come out, I'm just trying to figure out how model mix going forward and how that might relate to gross margins. Thanks guys.
Martin McDermut
We stopped the range for this coming quarter. We brought down you know the margins a little bit and that's because you will see a shift in the business between connectivity and computing. So I think as we said some headwinds going forward but it's to be stable in the last probably should be stable through the end of the year.
Paramesh Gopi
And to add to what Marty said if you go back and look at the margin band in our guidance we're walking the margin band up by a couple of percentage points every single quarter that should give you a good way to assess the robustness and underpinnings of the way we run our business.
